Test Case 1: Language Selection

Test Case Title: Language Selection

Test Case ID: LOC-01

Description: Verify that the application allows users to select their preferred language and that the app's content and user interface are displayed in the selected language.

Preconditions:

The application is installed and launched.
The user is on the settings screen (if applicable).
Test Steps:

Navigate to the application's settings 
Locate the edition selection option.
Select a different language from the available options (e.g., United States or Japanese).
Confirm the language change by saving the selection.
Verify that the app's content, including news articles and user interface elements, is displayed in the selected language.

Expected Results:

After selecting a language, all app content should be displayed in the chosen language.
